Scheme 3 Reaction schemes for the preparation of Schiff bases and associated keto-enol tautomerization.

dark. Absorbance was measured at $590 \mathrm{~nm}$. Cell inhibition was determined by the following equation:

\[
\% \text { cell inhibition }=100-\left\{\left(A_{\mathrm{t}}-A_{\mathrm{b}}\right) /\left(A_{\mathrm{c}}-A_{\mathrm{b}}\right)\right\} \times 100
\]

where, $A_{\mathrm{t}}=$ absorbance value of test compound, $A_{\mathrm{b}}=$ absorbance value of blank, $A_{\mathrm{c}}=$ absorbance value of control.

Absorbance values that are lower than the control cells indicate a reduction in the rate of cell proliferation. Conversely, a higher absorbance rate indicates an increase in cell proliferation. Rarely, an increase in proliferation may be offset by cell death; evidence of cell death may be inferred from morphological changes.

\[
\begin{gathered}
\% \text { cell survival }=\left\{\left(A_{\mathrm{t}}-A_{\mathrm{b}}\right) /\left(A_{\mathrm{c}}-A_{\mathrm{b}}\right)\right\} \times 100 \\
\% \text { cell inhibition }=100-\text { cell survival }
\end{gathered}
\]

